          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p>
                                        <add>כ"ה ניוארארק עלק פ כ"ג שבט תרי"ט</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N.Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>Friday</date>,</p>
                              <p>
                                        <date>Pericope Jethro (December)</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>(<date>1848</date>).</p>
                              <p>Peace, etc, etc to the</p>
                              <p><addressee>Rabbi Isaac Lehser</addressee> of
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Although for two years I have refrained<lb/> from
                                        writing about the New sect which is<lb/> called Reformers,
                                        but, nevertheless, at the<lb/> insistence of several people
                                        of great<lb/> piety, I could not refuse, and my<lb/>
                                        intention, is now to reply to the heretical<lb/> works which
                                        are appearing in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> every
                                        month and bear the name of<lb/> Sinai. I refer especially to
                                        the last<lb/> book which was published with regard to<lb/>
                                        uncovering the head at the time of the<lb/> grace after
                                        meals. That is why I ask<lb/> you dear Sir, to write to me
                                        on <date>Sunday</date><lb/> next whether you want to publish
                                        in the<lb/> Occident whatever I write. If so I shall<lb/>
                                        send it to you next week. Thus will I<lb/> know if I have
                                        found grace in your<lb/> eyes. Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Menachem</persName>, son
                                        of <persName>Leib</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)"><persName>Goldsmith</persName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">My address is <persName>Emanuel
                                                  Goldsmith</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <placeName>101 Chatham St., NY.</placeName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
